<br>
1) Armor that drops there is better than what is currently found in Hate/Fear (off normal mobs) and drops are much more common.<br>
<br>
2) I have destroyed my faction being there 4 times, but    haven't seen a consequence yet, deity is Karana not Tunare or whatever, but don't seem to be Kos anywhere I need to go.  I have heard faction can be repaired easily but don't have more info unfortunately.<br>
<br>
3)  Most mobs you face (not bosses or mini-bosses) are lvl 51 to 60 with a few being higher.  The group makeup the times I went were either 3 or 4 groups of 50 plus with usually two groups of 55 to 60 and one or two lower groups of 50 to 55.  I would seriously advise waiting until we have at least two enchanters, two clerics, and several tanks in the 55 and above category.<br>
<br>
4)  &quot;Breaking&quot; PoG is basically not required, I don't remember any mobs being able to see thru invisible, so groups can be organized and buffed outside, invised, zone in, and moved to the SW? corner without much difficulty.  If you haven't been to PoG and are a non evil race, you prolly won't even need invis the first time.<br>
<br>
5)  The biggest danger with PoG is the ever present Protectors of Growth.  These are two mobs, can be lvl 55 or 56, that spawn every 30 minutes like clockwork and hunt you down.  They can spawn basically anywhere in the zone exactly 30 minutes from the last time they died, but will find you no matter where you are.  They don't always spawn two, sometimes only one, but hit extremely hard, cannot be mezzed and are nearly impossible to taunt off.  They instantly smack anyone sitting, going from person to person, then usually find themselves a nice cleric or caster and beat them to nothing.  They can be rooted and the most commonly exploited tactic is to have a very high level pally pull one and root it while the groups kill the other.  Kiting also works if room is available, but this isn't typically an option when you first lose invis after setting up camp upon entry and await the protectors for the first of many encounters.  They also don't drop loot, so are basically just a menace.<br>
<br>
Oh well, just thought I would add some info on PoG.  It is definitely one of my favorite zones, and I would love to get back there once SGA is ready for it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showMessage?topicID=175.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showMessage?topicID=172.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=177.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/slate/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=177.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.threadControl?topicID=177.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/slate/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=177.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fsaryrnguildallianceboardfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=177.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="saryrnguildallianceboardfrm1">General Discussion<option value="saryrnguilda